  • Diagnosis. This species resembles a small A. vicina but the forewing fasciation is much narrower and the black suffusion of the hindwing is intense to the margin except for a narrow, dentate green zone at the margin itself. The male genitalia are similar to those of the species following, but the process from the valve costa is shallow, obtuse. (Source)

  • Habitat preference. The species is encountered infrequently in a range of lowland forest types. (Source)
